function canReach(arr, start) {
    if (start >= 0 && start < arr.length && arr[start] >= 0) {
        if (arr[start] === 0)
            return true;

        let jump = arr[start];
        arr[start] = -arr[start];
        return canReach(arr, start + jump) || canReach(arr, start - jump);
    }
    return false;
}
```

    The algorithm uses a depth-first search approach. At each index `i`, it checks if it's within the bounds of the array and if the value at the current index is non-negative.

If the current value is 0, it returns true because the goal is reached.
If not, it marks the current position as visited by negating the value and then checks if it can reach 0 with the available jump choices, `i + arr[i]` or `i - arr[i]`.

The function returns false if no valid path was found that reaches the 0 value.

